  "prompt": "Who is best hockey player of 2015?",
  "response": "In 2015, **Carey Price**, the goaltender for the Montreal Canadiens, was widely recognized as the best hockey player. He was awarded the **Hart Memorial Trophy**, which is given annually to the National Hockey League\u2019s (NHL) Most Valuable Player (MVP). Price's exceptional performance during the 2014-2015 NHL season solidified his reputation as one of the top goaltenders in the league.\n\nAdditionally, **Jamie Benn** of the Dallas Stars won the **Art Ross Trophy** in 2015 for being the NHL's leading scorer that season. Both players had standout seasons, but Carey Price's overall impact and contribution to his team's success earned him the MVP honors, making him a strong candidate for the title of the best hockey player of 2015.\n\n**Key Highlights of Carey Price\u2019s 2014-2015 Season:**\n- **Hart Memorial Trophy Winner** (MVP)\n- Led the NHL in **Goals Against Average (GAA)**\n- Ranked among the league leaders in **save percentage**\n- Played a pivotal role in Montreal Canadiens' strong defensive performance\n\nWhile other players like Sidney Crosby, Alexander Ovechkin, and Connor McDavid also had impressive seasons, Carey Price's outstanding goalkeeping and leadership were pivotal in earning him the top individual honor in 2015.",
